<b>Import targets via CSV</b>

<p>
  Use the form below to import targets via a CSV (comma separated value) file. All three fields must be present even if they are left blank.
  Do not use quotes around text in any field. Each row will be separated by a newline or carriage return.  e.g. title, output_text, description, content
</p>

<p>
  <b><i>Format example:</i></b><br />

  <code>
    country_norway, Norway, A little nip of Norway, http://www.norway.com<br />
    country_greece, Greece, A little spot of Greece, http://www.greece.com<br />
    country_hungary, Hungary, A little hunk of Hungary, http://www.hungary.com<br />
    country_turkey, Turkey, A little slice of Turkey, http://www.turkey.com<br />
  </code>

</p>

<div class="upload_form">
<% form_tag({:action => :import}, :multipart => true, :accept => "text/csv") do %>
  <p><label for="upload_file">Select File</label> :

  <%= file_field 'upload', 'datafile' %></p>
  <%= submit_tag "Upload" %>
<% end %>
</div>



